data.title: H-FISTA: Phase retrieval for pulsar spectroscopy
data.name: H-FISTA
data.description: Hierarchical FISTA - phase retrieval for pulsar spectroscopy

evidence: "H-FISTA accepts input data in ASCII format ... a FITS file, or a pickle. If using a notebook, you can use any custom reader as long as the data ends up in a NumPy array."
"To see how we used the code to produce the results in the paper, please see the notebooks included in this repostitory" and the listed notebooks show it is used to generate paper results.

"It is also possible to use the code on the command line. For example to reproduce the results for J0837+0610: `python HFISTA.py --data J0837+0610.fits --striation`" indicating direct execution from the cloned repository.
